Of course, this is a geometric sequence, so the ratio between any two consecutive terms is the same. This ratio is $\frac{\frac{i+1}{i+2}}{\frac{i}{i+1}}$. Clearly, this is $\frac{\left(i+1\right)^2}{i\left(i+2\right)}$</think>

<answer>
\begin{align*}
\text{The ratio is}\quad & \frac{i+1}{i+2}\cdot\frac{i+1}{i}\\
  & =\frac{\left(i+1\right)^2}{i\left(i+2\right)}
\end{align*}
<answer>
$\frac{\left(i+1\right)^2}{i\left(i+2\right)}$
</answer>

